-- Death Toll From Rainstorms in Southern China Climbs to 199, Ministry Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-22T05:39:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/death-toll-from-rainstorms-in-southern-china-climbs-to-199-ministry-says.html

          
          
             The death toll from rainstorms in
southern China rose to 199 as of 11 a.m. local time today, the
Ministry of Civil Affairs said on its website.  
 Another 123 people are missing, the ministry said. The
storms and resulting floods have caused 42.1 billion yuan of
economic losses, according to the ministryâ€™s statement.  
